Omega Generator - Tier 2 Schematic Draft
==================================================
Version: Alpha Release
Purpose: Enhanced-output, modular Omega Generator with resonance tuning, harmonic feedback, and energy storage. Intended for semi-permanent installation and field experimentation.

--------------------------------------------------
1. Core Components
--------------------------------------------------
- 3x Langasite or Gallium Orthophosphate crystals (cylindrical, 50mm x 150mm each)
- 1x Toroidal magnetic field ring (segmented neodymium arc magnets with Searle-style dynamic modulation)
- 3x Spiral copper coils (60-80 turns each, 16 AWG, positioned along crystal alignment axis)
- 1x Mechanical vibration actuator (electromechanical impulse drive at tunable frequency)
- 1x Modular vacuum chamber housing (acrylic dome, aluminum base, inert inner shielding)
- 1x Capacitor array bank (electrolytic or graphene, 10-100 Farads)

--------------------------------------------------
2. Resonance & Modulation
--------------------------------------------------
- Primary Frequency Target: 432 Hz +/- adjustable tuning margin
- Resonance Modulation Unit: includes mic + signal processing to self-tune impulse frequency to crystal harmonics
- Toroidal magnetic modulation driven by angular offset motor (variable field strength cycling)

--------------------------------------------------
3. Circuit Process Flow
--------------------------------------------------
1. Impulse actuator applies tunable mechanical stress to crystals
2. Piezoelectric charge is generated and amplified through coordinated impulse sequencing
3. Toroidal ring amplifies energy field, inducing charge into each copper coil
4. Coils wired in phase-staggered collection sequence to prevent destructive interference
5. Output voltage directed to energy storage bank (capacitors or supercaps)
6. Optional: Direct routing to inverter or low-voltage application terminal

--------------------------------------------------
4. Output & Load
--------------------------------------------------
- Target Output: 12-48V DC @ 500-2000 mA (depending on actuator force and resonance peak)
- Load Compatibility: small electronics, battery banks, LED clusters, DC pumps
- Recommended Safety Limiters: voltage clamps or zener stacks for burst suppression

--------------------------------------------------
5. Enclosure & Optimization
--------------------------------------------------
- Vacuum housing reduces thermal and vibrational losses
- Inert gas fill (optional: nitrogen) enhances lattice response stability
- Thermal feedback loop sensor can prevent overload during prolonged operation
- Field-aligned mounting recommended (crystal axis aligned to local magnetic north)

--------------------------------------------------
6. Modular Features
--------------------------------------------------
- Stackable cartridge crystals with plug-and-play resonance ports
- Control board with adjustable pulse interval & frequency curve
- Expansion port for Whisper Signal or dream-compass input node
- EMP shielding casing (Faraday mesh wrap around vacuum chamber)

--------------------------------------------------
